---
/* /websites — the website build, as a standalone service. Owner-and-money
   voice, plain and straight: every visitor who leaves is a job → the enemy
   (the brochure) → most sites only sell the 1 in 10 who's ready; I build for
   the 9 → the 24/7 salesman → see-it-first risk reversal → two build tiers →
   then the bundle (Done For You) that includes this same site plus the Google
   work. Highlighter on light sections only. */
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CTAButton from '../components/CTAButton.astro';
import StickyMobileCTA from '../components/StickyMobileCTA.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site.config';

const minutes = site.callLengthMinutes;
const bookHref = '/book';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="See-It-First Website Build for Kitchen & Bath | Kitchen Websites"
  description="Most homeowners who land on your site are just looking. I build the website that turns them into the ones who call. See the whole thing before you pay a dollar. Kitchen and bath only."
>
  <!-- 1 — HERO -->
  <section class="section web-hero">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">The website build · Kitchen &amp; bath only</p>
      <h1 class="web-hero__h1">A website that turns your visitors into booked jobs.</h1>
      <p class="lede web-hero__sub">Most homeowners who land on your site are just looking. I build the site that turns them into the ones who call. <span class="hl">You see the whole thing before you pay a dollar.</span></p>
      <div class="web-hero__cta">
        <CTAButton href={bookHref} label="Schedule your free strategy session" event="Web:HeroToBook" size="lg" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 2–6 — THE LETTER -->
  <section class="section web-body">
    <div class="container container--prose web-prose">
      <h2 class="web-h">Every visitor who leaves is a job walking out.</h2>
      <p>A homeowner lands on your site, feels nothing, and clicks away.</p>
      <p>That wasn’t a lost click. That was a kitchen. Twenty or thirty thousand dollars, gone before you knew it showed up.</p>
      <p class="web-beat"><span class="hl">A few of those a month adds up to tens of thousands a year. It goes to your competitor instead of you.</span></p>

      <h2 class="web-h">It’s not your work. It’s what’s speaking for it.</h2>
      <p>Your work is good. Everyone who has hired you knows it.</p>
      <p>The site most contractors get sold doesn’t show it. A pretty brochure. A stock kitchen that was never yours. A template she has already seen on ten other contractors this week.</p>
      <p>It makes the best builder in town look like the cheapest. She can’t tell you apart, so she picks the lowest price.</p>
      <p class="web-beat"><span class="hl">Your site sells for you when you’re not there. Right now it’s costing you jobs.</span></p>

      <h2 class="web-h">Most sites only sell to the one already sold.</h2>
      <p>Ten homeowners land on your site. One is ready to call today. The other nine are still deciding.</p>
      <p>Most contractor sites are built for that one. A few photos, a phone number, a form. They do nothing for the other nine.</p>
      <p>Those nine are most of the money you could be making.</p>
      <p class="web-punch">I build for the nine.</p>
      <p>The site shows her the kitchen she has been picturing. It answers the questions she is worried about. It gives her enough proof to stop shopping around and call you.</p>
      <p class="web-beat"><span class="hl">She lands just looking. She leaves ready to call.</span></p>

      <h2 class="web-h">Your best salesman, and it never sleeps.</h2>
      <p>It sells while you’re on the job. It sells at eleven at night, while she is deciding who to call in the morning.</p>
      <p>It never takes a day off. It never works for your competitor.</p>
      <p>Your real kitchens in front of her. Reviews from her area. Your number one tap away. It closes her while you’re across town on another job.</p>
      <p class="web-beat"><span class="hl">It works every day, and you pay for it once.</span></p>

      <h2 class="web-h">I build it first. You pay after you’ve seen it.</h2>
      <p>You’ve paid a marketer up front and got nothing back. Not here.</p>
      <p>I design your homepage before you owe me a dollar. Your kitchens, your name, the real thing on your screen.</p>
      <p>If you like it, I build the rest at one flat price. If you don’t, it cost you nothing.</p>
      <p class="web-beat"><span class="hl">You can’t lose money on a site you saw before you paid for it.</span></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 7 — TWO TIERS -->
  <section class="section section--sm web-tiers">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="web-tiers__h">Two ways to build it. Both see-it-first. Both yours to keep.</h2>
      <div class="web-tiers__grid">
        <article class="tier">
          <p class="tier__name">Standard</p>
          <p class="tier__price">$1,500</p>
          <p class="tier__for">The site most shops need. Built to convert, live fast.</p>
          <ul class="tier__list">
            <li>Five pages: home, services, gallery, about, contact</li>
            <li>A proven layout that turns lookers into callers</li>
            <li>Your real kitchens, reviews, and services loaded in</li>
            <li>Quote form and click-to-call on every page</li>
            <li>Fast on mobile, where she’s looking</li>
            <li>Live in about two weeks</li>
            <li>You see it before you pay a dollar</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
        <article class="tier tier--featured">
          <p class="tier__name">Custom</p>
          <p class="tier__price">$4,500</p>
          <p class="tier__for">For the shop that wants to look like the top of the market.</p>
          <ul class="tier__list">
            <li>A design built from scratch, a look nobody else in town has</li>
            <li>Every service on its own page, built to rank and convert</li>
            <li>Full project galleries with before-and-afters</li>
            <li>Room to sell: your process, your story, your guarantees</li>
            <li>Financing, online booking, or live chat added if you want it</li>
            <li>Built so you look like the high-end choice right away</li>
            <li>You see it before you pay a dollar</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
      <p class="web-tiers__note">Most shops start with Standard. Choose Custom if you’re a high-end shop and your site needs to show it right away.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 8 — THIS PAGE IS JUST THE WEBSITE; DONE FOR YOU IS THE BUNDLE -->
  <section class="section section--sm web-plan">
    <div class="container container--prose web-prose">
      <h2 class="web-h">This page is just the website. Done For You is everything.</h2>
      <p>A website on its own brings you more jobs. But it only works on the homeowners who already found you.</p>
      <p>Done For You is the full package. It includes this same website, plus your Google rebuilt and run every month, a steady stream of reviews, AI search, and the guarantee that more homeowners call or I work for free.</p>
      <p>One package, $750 a month, and you own all of it.</p>
      <div class="web-cta"><CTAButton href="/done-for-you" label="See everything Done For You includes" event="WebToDoneForYou" /></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <StickyMobileCTA href={bookHref} label={`Book the ${minutes}-minute call`} event="Web:StickyToBook" />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* highlighter — translucent stroke BEHIND the text, light sections only */
  .hl { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 30%, transparent); box-decoration-break: clone; -webkit-box-decoration-break: clone; padding: 0.08em 0.18em; border-radius: 2px; }

  .web-hero { padding-top: var(--space-12); text-align: center; }
  .web-hero__h1 { margin: var(--space-4) auto 0; max-width: 20ch; }
  .web-hero__sub { margin: var(--space-5) auto 0; max-width: 54ch; }
  .web-hero__cta { margin-top: var(--space-8); display: flex; justify-content: center; }

  .web-h { margin-top: var(--space-10); font-size: var(--fs-h3); }
  .web-cta { margin-top: var(--space-6); }
  .web-prose p { margin-top: var(--space-4); font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: var(--fs-bodyL); line-height: 1.7; color: var(--ink); }
  .web-prose h2 + p { margin-top: var(--space-5); }
  /* display punch line (no highlighter) */
  .web-prose .web-punch { margin-top: var(--space-5); font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: var(--fw-display); font-size: var(--fs-h4); letter-spacing: -0.01em; line-height: 1.2; color: var(--ink); }

  /* two build tiers */
  .web-tiers__h { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: var(--fw-display); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: var(--tracking-display); font-size: var(--fs-h3); line-height: 1.1; text-align: center; max-width: 26ch; margin-inline: auto; }
  .web-tiers__grid { margin-top: var(--space-8); display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: var(--space-5); align-items: start; }
  @media (min-width: 48em) { .web-tiers__grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: var(--space-6); } }
  .tier { background: var(--bg-raised); border: var(--rule-width) solid var(--line); border-top: var(--rule-thick) solid var(--accent); border-radius: var(--radius-sm); padding: var(--space-8); }
  .tier--featured { border: var(--rule-thick) solid var(--ink); box-shadow: 6px 6px 0 var(--rule-soft); }
  .tier__name { font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: var(--fs-caption); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: var(--tracking-caps); font-weight: var(--fw-body-semi); color: var(--accent-deep); }
  .tier__price { margin-top: var(--space-2); font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: var(--fw-display); font-size: var(--fs-h2); line-height: 1; color: var(--ink); }
  .tier__for { margin-top: var(--space-3); font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: var(--fs-body); line-height: 1.5; color: var(--ink-70); }
  .tier__list { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: var(--space-5) 0 0; display: grid; gap: var(--space-3); }
  .tier__list li { position: relative; padding-left: var(--space-5); font-size: var(--fs-body-sm); line-height: 1.5; color: var(--ink); }
  .tier__list li::before { content: ""; position: absolute; left: 0; top: 0.6em; width: 12px; height: 2px; background: var(--accent); }
  .web-tiers__note { margin: var(--space-8) auto 0; max-width: 60ch; text-align: center; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: var(--fs-body); line-height: 1.6; color: var(--ink-70); }
</style>
